 Cross Game is a romantic comedy sports manga series written and illustrated by Mitsuru Adachi and published by Shogakukan. It began serialization in the 22/23 2005 issue (11 May 2005) of the sh&lt;U+014D&gt;nen manga magazine Weekly Sh&lt;U+014D&gt;nen Sunday,1 and is still on-going. , its individual chapters have been collected into 15 tank&lt;U+014D&gt;bon volumes.2 The series is about the high school baseball players K&lt;U+014D&gt; Kitamura and Aoba Tsukishima and their attempts to fulfill the dream of Aoba's dead sister, Wakaba, of seeing them play in the national championship tournament in K&lt;U+014D&gt;shien. In 2009, it received the Shogakukan Manga Award for sh&lt;U+014D&gt;nen manga.3
The series is divided into multiple parts. Part One, &quot;Wakaba's Season&quot;, consists solely of volume one, and takes place while the main characters are in elementary school. Part Two, &quot;Aoba's Season&quot;, consists of volumes two through fourteen. It begins four years later with K&lt;U+014D&gt; in his third year of junior high school and continues into high school. In Part Two, the chapter numbering begins again from one. In October 2008, the series went on hiatus at the end of Part Two4 and was resumed in March 2009 with Part Three, as-yet untitled, beginning with K&lt;U+014D&gt; in the summer of his third year of high school.
The series was adapted into an anime television series that began airing on the TV Tokyo network on 5 April 2009 and is still broadcasting.5 The manga is licensed in France by Editions Tonkam,6 in Italy by Flashbook Editore,7 in South Korea by Daiwon C.I.,8 in Hong Kong by Jonesky,9 in Taiwan by Chingwin Publishing Group,10 in Indonesia by Elex Media Komputindo,11 and in Thailand by Vibulkij Publishing.12 __TOC__ {{-}}
